- In this metaphor, 'students' are referred to as 'voyagers', 'core courses' as 'essential milestones', and 'academic programs' as 'journeys'.;
- The 'core' category in the database corresponds to vital lessons that are essential for advancement in the program.;
- A 'journey' is completed when the voyager has passed through a sufficient number of essential milestones, here defined as five or more.
